cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.OS, cs.DC, cs.AR 

This paper discusses a new side-channel attack that targets the operating system page cache, which is a fundamental software cache in modern computer systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also proposes mitigations for some of the attacks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper discusses the page cache, which is a component of the operating system, indicating that it could belong to cs.OS (Operating Systems). The paper also mentions the spatial and temporal resolution of the attack, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper discusses a low profile remote covert channel, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
